Geometriniai objektai (geomai)

Geomai

# Pirmasis 
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
    geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) 

# Antrasis 
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
    geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

Geom ir estetini element (ne)suderinamumas

ggplot(data = mpg) +
    geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ,
                              y = hwy,
                              linetype = drv))

ggplot2 ir j papildantys paketai

https://www.ggplot2-exts.org

Estetikos elementas group

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, group = drv))

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_smooth(
    mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = drv),
    show.legend = FALSE
  )

Keli geomai tame paiame grafike

ggplot(data = mpg) + 
    geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
    geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

Keli geomai tame paiame grafike: raome glausiau

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth()

Numatytojo idstymo papildymas ar pakeitimas

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = class)) + 
   geom_smooth()

Numatytj duomen keitimas

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
    geom_point(mapping = aes(color = class)) + 
    geom_smooth(data = filter(mpg, class == "subcompact"), se = FALSE)

Uduotys: Geomai

  1. Kur geom naudosite braiyti:
    • Linij grafik? geom_line ()
    • Staiakamp diagram (boxplot)? geom_boxplot()
    • Histogram? geom_histogram()
    • Sklaidos diagram (scatterplot)? geom_scatterplot()
  2. Mintimis vykdykite kod ir nuspkite rezultat. Tik po to patikrinkite, ar js mintys sutapo su tikruoju atsakymu.
  1. Viename i io skyriaus grafik buvo panaudotas argumentas show.legend = FALSE. K jis daro? Kas vyksta j paalinus? Kodl jis buvo naudotas ankstesniuose pavyzdiuose?
Panaudojant  argument neberodoma legenda. J paalinus legenda yra matoma.
  1. K atlieka se argumentas funkcijoje geom_smooth()?
se - rodomas patikimumo intervalas ties kreivs linija.
  1. Ar ie 2 grafikai atrodys skirtingai? Kodl? Atrodys taip pat. Pirmasis pateikimas yra antrojo sutrumpinta versija.
  1. Paraykite R kod, kuris braio iuos eis grafikus
knitr::include_graphics("parasykite-koda-grafikams.png")

# Grafikas 1
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
    geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
    geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

# Grafikas 2
ggplot(data = mpg) + geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, group = drv))

# Grafikas 3
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = drv)) +
geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, group =drv, color = drv))

# Grafikas 4
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = drv)) +
geom_smooth()

# Grafikas 5
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(color = drv)) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(linetype = drv)) 

# Grafikas 6
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = drv))
